1.title: The Big Picture

episode of.title: The Rise with Dr. Travis Fox (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: From graffiti offender to award winning artists, the Big Picture Arts program helps rehabilitate those who were caught for graffiti. Artist Andrew Johnstone shows us what goes into the program and where his inspiration comes from for the program and we talk with current and former students of his program-- On this episode of The Rise.

2.plot: On this episode of TheRise, Aj tells his personal story of growth and developing his theories to improve your golf game. His story is the exact opposite of "The Blind Side" - His life was changed by attending an all black school and being saved by his classmates. These lessons from a professional Caddy are amazing!

4.title: Still Rollin'

episode of.title: The Rise with Dr. Travis Fox (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: On this episode of TheRise, we travel down to sunny San Diego where we meet up with skateboarding legend Victor Earhart. He shows us the technology behind the scenes at Sector9 Skateboards that goes into the manufacturing process and how a piece of wood becomes a skateboard that is being used around the world. He shares some of his wisdom on life- wisdom that us, here at TheRise, have never heard. Also, Victor takes out our Director Jamie Knapp and teaches him how to keep rolling when skateboarding. 5.title: Living Life in Costa Rica

episode of.title: The Rise with Dr. Travis Fox (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: On this episode of TheRise, we are in Costa Rica and we talk with Sam Patterson about how he 'woke up' one day and gave up his life in the United States and moved to Costa Rica. He purchased a farm that covers hundreds of acres of untouched land and decided to create his own adventure park called Pura Aventura. We go for a run on the Zip lines and talk with Sam about how he is Rising Up from Costa Rica!
